                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_ʒækʼæn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ʒækʼæn</orth><form type="variant"><orth>zækʼæn</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ʒækʼænæ</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>кизяк</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (высушенный навоз, употребляемый как топливо)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (pressed dung used as fuel)</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>kizyak</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (высушенный навоз, употребляемый как топливо)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (pressed dung used as fuel)</note></sense><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*sakan-</w></mentioned> и сближается с рядом индоиранских слов: <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>śaknás</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/> <w>saγan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/> <w>saγön</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/> <w>skan</w> <gloss><q>помет крупного рогатого скота</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/> <w>sigin</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/> <w>sakin</w></mentioned> и др. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>). Несмотря на некоторые фонетические „странности“ (начальный %iʒ%i из %is%i, появление смычно-гортанного %ikʼ%i), этимология вряд ли может быть оспариваема. Что начальный %is%i существовал в прошлом в осетинском, подтверждается косвенно <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>səgən</w> <gloss><q>кизяк</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. также <mentioned xml:lang="inc-x-mid"><lang/> <w>čhagana-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inc-x-mid"><w>čhakana</w> <gloss><q>кизяк</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Mayrhofer"/></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Mayrhofer"/></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, а за пределами арийского — <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><lang/> <w>šakkan-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><w>šakkar-</w> <gloss><q>экскременты</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*sakan-</w></mentioned> and relates to a number of Indo-European words: <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>śaknás</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/> <w>saγan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/> <w>saγön</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/> <w>skan</w> <gloss><q>cattle excrements</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/> <w>sigin</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/> <w>sakin</w></mentioned> etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>). Despite some phonect “oddities” (initial %iʒ%i from %is%i, appearance of an ejective %ikʼ%i), the etymology can hardly be disputed. The fact that the initial %is%i existed in the past in Ossetic is confirmed indirectle by <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>səgən</w> <gloss><q>kizyak</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. also <mentioned xml:lang="inc-x-mid"><lang/> <w>čhagana-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inc-x-mid"><w>čhakana</w> <gloss><q>kizyak</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Mayrhofer"/></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Mayrhofer"/></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, and paprt from Aryan — <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><lang/> <w>šakkan-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><w>šakkar-</w> <gloss><q>excrements</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>